oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Godzilla topiary
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Slide film (or reversal film) of a Godzilla topiary located at a park in Tokyo, Japan. Emiko and Yasko, who were governesses for the Kinsall family, are pictured with the Kinsall children, Robert (aged 2) and Lucinda (aged 3.)

Godzilla is a Japanese kaiju film, which was the first film in the Godzilla franchise. It was released in Nagoya, Japan on October 27, 1954 and nationwide on November 3, 1954. The film spawned a multimedia franchise and is the longest running film franchise in the world.
